# main-frontend architecture

This document describes the architecture of the **main-frontend** web app (Next.js + React + TypeScript) as implemented in this repository.

## What this app does

`main-frontend` is the primary 99Notes portal UI.

- It uses Next.js App Router under `src/app/`.
- It renders a public site with a navigation/footer layout and also contains dashboard/operator flows under a no-navbar layout group.
- It uses cookies for authentication in coordination with the backend(s).

## Tech stack

- Framework: Next.js (App Router)
- UI: React + TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Data: `fetch` wrapper in `src/config/api/route.ts`

## Runtime entrypoints

- `src/app/layout.tsx`
  - Root HTML layout and global providers.
  - Wraps the app in an `AuthProvider` and includes `AuthModal`.

- `src/app/(use-navbar)/layout.tsx`
  - Layout group that renders Navbar + Footer and loads navigation/footer sections.

- `src/app/(no-navbar)/layout.tsx`
  - Layout group for dashboard/operator flows without the main navbar/footer.

## Routing (App Router)

- Public site pages live under `src/app/(use-navbar)/...`.
- Dashboard/operator pages live under `src/app/(no-navbar)/...`.

## API boundary

- API client: `src/config/api/route.ts`
  - Uses `fetch` with `credentials: "include"`.
  - Base URL is centralized in a single config module (avoid scattering base URLs across components).
  - Central place to control headers and request options.

## High-level architecture

- `src/components/` contains reusable UI components.
- `src/lib/` contains utilities and data helpers (e.g., navigation fetching).
- `src/contexts/` contains auth-related providers.

## Local development

- `npm run dev`
- `npm run build`
- `npm start`

